Before Definition â€“ Letâ€™s Understand the Problem

Before we jump into any formal definition,
letâ€™s first understand the real problem Git solves.

Problem 1: Managing Code as a Solo Developer

Even if you are working alone, managing code is difficult.

You face problems like:
Multiple versions of your code
No proper history of changes
No clear backup
Confusion like: â€œWhich file was correct?â€

As your project grows, these problems grow too.
----------
Problem 2: Working in a Team

Now imagine working in a team:
5 developers
