---------------------------------------

Simple Definition of Git

Now letâ€™s look at the definition.

Git is a free and open-source distributed version control system,
designed to handle everything from small to very large projects
with speed and efficiency.

The important words here are:
Distributed Version Control System

-------------------------------------------
Types of Version Control Systems

There are mainly three types:

1. Local Version Control
Multiple copies of the same project
Everything stored on one system
Very risky
Not recommended

2. Central Version Control
One central server
Team sends changes to it
But local history is limited

3. Distributed Version Control (Git)
This is what Git uses.
In Git:
every developer has full project history locally
online repository also has full history
everyone stays in sync
This makes Git very powerful and safe.

------------------

